name: RT_ENGINESPEED
long_desc: Engine Speed in rpm as measured by the crankshaft sensor. This is the primary input for the fuel and ignition maps

name: RT_ENGINESPEEDSITE
long_desc: The engine speed is converted into an index by the Speed Index Map. This index is used to access the main fuel and ignition maps. You should not edit this map directly but adjust the axis values on a map that uses Engine Speed (Eg TPS vs Speed Ign Map).

name: RT_SOFTCUTTIME
long_desc: Shows what the ECU is using as the soft cut threshold.

name: RT_HARDCUTTIME
long_desc: Shows what the ECU is using as the hard cut threshold.

name: RT_WHEELSPEEDREVLIMIT
long_desc: Rev Limit from road speed

name: RT_REVOLUTIONCOUNTER
long_desc: The number of revolutions since the engine was last stopped. Limited at 65534.

name: RT_REVCOUNTERINDEX
long_desc: The output of the RC Index map. Provides a site number for properties that are dependent on the length of the time the engine has been running.

name: RT_DSPEEDBYDT_1

name: RT_DSPEEDBYDT_2

name: RT_ENGINESPEEDSITE_8

name: RT_UPPERCAMWINDOW

name: RT_MEASUREDCAM1PHASE
long_desc: Measured Cam 1 Phase. This shows the angle after TDC Firing No 1 to the Cam Edge. If the Crank Sensor Position Offset is positive then the ECU will sync with the Cam Phase as a poitive number. Likewise if the Crank Sensor Position Offset is negative then the ECU will sync with the Cam Phase as a negative number.

long_desc: The amount of compensation that is subtracted each revolution of the engine. This value is a function of the coolant temperature and engine speed.

name: RT_ACCELFUELGAIN
long_desc: Accel Fuel Gain

name: RT_BLATTIMER
long_desc: Async Accel Timer. Timer showing how long until Lambda control can be established.

name: RT_BLATFACTOR
long_desc: Async Fuel Factor. This the the factor applied to the Async Accel Pulse Width Map; to calculate the amount of Async Fuel Required. This comes from the Async Accel Factor Map.

name: RT_BLATFACTORINDEX
long_desc: Async Accel Index. Based on Rate of Change of the input to the Accel Fuel System; this is the index used as the input for the Async Accel Factor Map

name: RT_BLATFUELFROMMAP
long_desc: Async Accel Fuel from Map

name: RT_BLATFUELATINJECTOR
long_desc: Async Accel Fuel at Injector

name: RT_FUELTIMINGFROMMAP
long_desc: The injection stop time read from the map

name: RT_FUELTIMINGFROMMAPPLUSTRIM
short_desc: Inj Stop time from map plus trim
long_desc: The injection stop time read from the map after being trimmed by the mapping knob

name: RT_INJSTARTANGLE
long_desc: The number of degrees before TDC that the injector opens.

name: RT_INJECTORSTOPANGLE
long_desc: The number of degrees before TDC that the injector closes.

name: RT_INJECTIONTIMEAINDEGS
long_desc: The time the set of injectors allocated to bank A are on for in degrees; after the battery voltage compensation has been added.

name: RT_CURRENTLAMBDAA
long_desc: The measurement of lambda from the sensor.

name: RT_CURRENTLAMBDAB
long_desc: The measurement of lambda from the sensor.

name: RT_TARGETLAMBDAFROMMAP
long_desc: The base lambda value that the ECU will attempt to control to. This number is normally derived from the Target Lambda map; but can be configured to come from a knob on the mapping box. If the Target Lambda is close to 0.00 or 2.55 then control will be disabled.

name: RT_EGTLAMBDATRIM
long_desc: EGT Lambda Trim. This is the trim applied to the lambda target as a result of the EGT control system.

name: RT_TARGETLAMBDA
long_desc: The lambda value that the ECU will attempt to control to. This includes the trim from the EGT system. This number is normally derived from the Target Lambda map; but can be configured to come from a knob on the mapping box. If the Target Lambda is close to 0.00 or 2.55 then control will be disabled.

name: RT_TPSVARIANCE2
long_desc: TPS Variance. An arbitray measure of TPS stability; it's primary use is to ascertain if conditions are sufficiently stable to enable closed loop fuel control.

name: RT_DSPEEDBYONEREVLAMBDACONTROL
short_desc: Max Rate of Change of Engine Speed for Lambda
long_desc: Max Rate of Change of Engine Speed for Lambda  Output of map.

name: RT_WARMUPTIMER
long_desc: Lambda control is disabled until a number of seconds have elapsed since the engine was started. This timer counts down from the initial value to zero.

name: RT_LAMBDAINTTERM1
long_desc: Short Term Trim. Shows the current corection made to fuellng in order to acheive Target Lambda.

name: RT_ECTBASEDSTARTTIMER
long_desc: ECT Based Start Timer

name: RT_LAMBDASTATUS(D)
long_desc: Displays whether or not the ECU is doing closed loop lambda control on Channel D. If this value is non-zero; lambda control is disabled. The bit field will indicate the reason why. See the other parameters in this section for more detail.

name: RT_LAMBDAINTTERM2
long_desc: Short Term Trim B. Shows the current corection made to fuellng in order to acheive Target Lambda.

name: RT_ADAPTIVEMAP1OUTPUT
long_desc: The Interpolated Output of the Adaptive Fuel Map.

name: RT_ADAPTIVEMAP2OUTPUT
long_desc: This realtime parameter has no information associated with it.

name: RT_ADAPTIVEFACTOR1
long_desc: I store + P Term + WIGLE Term . Not Shown.

name: RT_ADAPTIVEFACTOR2
long_desc: This realtime parameter has no information associated with it.

name: RT_ADAPTEDFUEL1
long_desc: The fuel pulse width for Bank 1 after all compensations have been applied including lambda/adaptive. The Upper/Lower split is appllied to this number followed by the Battery Voltage offset to give the final injection time.

name: RT_ADAPTEDFUEL2
long_desc: The fuel pulse width for Bank 2 after all compensations have been applied including lambda/adaptive. The Upper/Lower split is appllied to this number followed by the Battery Voltage offset to give the final injection time.

name: RT_SPLITRATIO(TPS/SPEED)
long_desc: The percentage of fuel that will go to the Upper injectors as read from the Split Map

name: RT_SPLITRATIO
long_desc: The percentage of fuel that will go to the Upper Injectors taking into account the Mapping Box setup and whether the ECU has been configured to run Upper Injectors. Note; the Split Ratio is not used during cranking.

name: RT_UPPERBATTERYVOLTAGECOMP
long_desc: The extra number of milliseconds that each injector is held open for due to the battery voltage. This parameter will appear GREEN during cranking

name: RT_INJECTIONTIMEUPPERA
long_desc: The time the set of upper injectors allocated to bank A are on for in milliseconds; after the battery voltage compensation has been added.

name: RT_INJECTIONTIMEUPPERB
long_desc: The time the set of upper injectors allocated to bank B are on for in milliseconds; after the battery voltage compensation has been added.

name: RT_PRECRANKFUEL
long_desc: The injection pulse width applied to all the injectors as the engine first starts to crank.

name: RT_DUTYCYCLEA
long_desc: The time that the injectors are on for divided by the time for 1 cycle (sequential).

name: RT_DUTYCYCLEB
long_desc: The time that the injectors allocated to bank B are on for divided by the time for 1 revolution (grouped) or 1 cycle (sequential).

name: RT_DUTYCYCLEUPPERA
long_desc: The time that the upper injectors allocated to bank A are on for divided by the time for 1 revolution (grouped) or 1 cycle (sequential).

name: RT_DUTYCYCLEUPPERB
long_desc: The time that the upper injectors allocated to bank B are on for divided by the time for 1 revolution (grouped) or 1 cycle (sequential).

name: RT_TARGETBOOST
long_desc: The boost pressure that the closed loop controller is trying to attain. This is primarily derived from the Target Boost Map but is affected by various compensations as well as demands from other ECUs such as a gearbox controller.

name: RT_TARGETBOOSTFROMMAP
long_desc: The output of the TPS vs Speed Target Boost Map before any compensations are applied.

name: RT_TARGETBOOSTPLUSTRIM
long_desc: The output of the TPS vs Speed Target Boost Map after being trimmed by the mapping box.

name: RT_AIRTEMPTARGETBOOST
long_desc: Shows the change in target boost pressure as a result of the air temperature.

name: RT_COOLANTTEMPTARGETBOOST
long_desc: Shows the change in target boost pressure as a result of the Coolant temperature.

name: RT_BOOSTERROR
long_desc: The closed loop boost controller subtracts the measured Manifold Pressure from the target boost pressure to get this term.

name: RT_BOOSTPTERM
long_desc: The result of the Error Term multiplied by the Proportional Gain. You would not normally need to monitor this parameter.

name: RT_BOOSTITERMH
long_desc: The upper word of the integral term of the boost controller. You would not normally need to monitor this parameter.

name: RT_BOOSTITERML
long_desc: The lower word of the integral term of the boost controller. You would not normally need to monitor this parameter.

name: RT_BOOSTISTOREH
long_desc: The upper word of the integral store of the boost controller. You would not normally need to monitor this parameter.

name: RT_BOOSTISTOREL
long_desc: The lower word of the integral store of the boost controller. You would not normally need to monitor this parameter.

name: RT_WASTEGATEOLDUTYCYCLE
long_desc: The open loop duty cycle is the starting point for the closed loop boost controller.

name: RT_WASTEGATEDUTYCYCLE
long_desc: The duty cycle applied to the waste gate valve. When running closed loop boost control this number comes from the closed loop controller. When in open loop mode it comes from the Open Loop Duty Cycle map. It can also come from a mapping knob.

name: RT_VARCAM1TARGET

name: RT_CAM1ERROR

name: RT_CAM2PHASE
long_desc: Var Cam2 Phase

name: RT_VARCAM2TARGET
long_desc: The cam position that the ECU is trying to attain

name: RT_CAM2ERROR

name: RT_VARCAM2DC

long_desc: The upper word of the intergral term of the variable cam control loop

name: RT_VARCAM1INTSTOREH
long_desc: The upper word of the intergral store of the variable cam control loop

name: RT_CURRENTFAULTSA

name: RT_CURRENTFAULTSB

name: RT_CURRENTFAULTSC

name: RT_INJECTOROPENCIRCUIT
long_desc: If the bit is set then there is an open circuit fault for that injector

name: RT_INJECTORSHORTCIRCUIT

name: RT_LOGGEDFAULTSA

name: RT_LOGGEDFAULTSB

name: RT_OUTPUTTORQUE

name: 1D_USERENGINEOFFSET
long_desc: Crank Sensor Position Offset determines the position of the Ignition and Fuel with repect to the Crank Sensor and (Primary) Missing tooth Angular Position (A Larger Number Advances the Ignition and Fuel). The reference tooth is the last tooth before the (primary) missing tooth/teeth. It should be set such that with the Engine stationary at TDC. Measure the Angle between the reference tooth and the Crank Sensor (in the direction of engine rotation).  Note that you can set the Crank Sensor Position Offset to any angle between -360 and +360degs. If the CAM edge occurs in the expansion or exhaust stroke of Cylinder#1 then you must set the Crank Sensor Position Offset between 0 and +360degs. If the CAM edge occurs in the intake or compression of Cylinder#1 then you must set the Crank Sensor Position Offset between 0 and -360degs.            Example values for I4: Rising Edge: 60-2 VX 228 Deg. 60-2 Peugeot 219 Deg. Falling Edge: 60-2 VW 82 Deg. 36-1 Ford 2.0L Duratec 263 Deg. 24-1 Busa  227 Deg. 24-2 Busa 211 Deg. Rover K 33 Deg. 24-1 Busa V8 (V-72) 120 Deg; (V-108) 48 Deg.

name: 1D_CRANKINGIGNITIONADVANCE
long_desc: Cranking Ignition Advance. If the engine is turning at a speed less than the <Crank Exit Speed> (i.e. Cranking); the ignition angle is derived only from the <Cranking Ignition advance>. Sample values for I4:60-2 VX +8 Deg. 60-2 VW +8 Deg. 36-1 Ford +8 Deg. 24-1 Busa 0 Deg. 24-2 Busa 0 Deg. Rover K +10Deg.

name: 1D_CRANKEXITSPEED
long_desc: The threshold at which the ECU changes from Cranking Maps to Running maps. Once the engine speed is above this number the ECU will not go back into cranking until the speed goes below the Crank Entry Speed. If the number is not in the range 350 -> 1000 rpm; the ECU will use a default of 650 rpm

name: 1D_CRANKENTRYSPEED
long_desc: The threshold at which the ECU changes from Running maps to Cranking Maps. If the Engine speed is below this number the ECU will remain in cranking mode until the speed exceeds the Crank Exit Speed. If the number is not in the range 350 -> 1000 rpm; the ECU will use the Crank Exit Speed.

name: 1D_USERMAXPOWERHOLDTIME
long_desc: Max Power Hold Time. This is the maximum length of time that the ECU will remain awake for after the ignition has been turned off. See <When Ign is Switched Off> for details

name: 1D_FUELEACHCYCLE_THRESHOLD
long_desc: Fuel Each Cycle Threshold. If Fuel Every Rev is enabled then the engine will always run Fuel Each Cycle above this threshold. This overrules the Fuel Every Rev Strategy 'Always'. At higher injector duty cycles time is lost if the injectors are opened each rev; by only opening each cycle better control of the fuel is achieved.

name: 1D_SOFTCUT
long_desc: Though there are many functions within the ECU that may limit the engine speed (e.g. Launch; Pit Lane Speed Limiter; Traction control function etc.) this  limiter is used as the absolute maximum speed. The Soft Cut invokes a random cut that does not upset the balance of the car. The Hard Cut disables all ignition or fuel above this engine speed. The optimum difference between the soft and hard cut is normally about 50 - 100 rpm.

name: 1D_HARDCUT
long_desc: Though there are many functions within the ECU that may limit the engine speed (e.g. Launch; Pit Lane Speed Limiter; Traction control function etc.) this  limiter is used as the absolute maximum speed. The Soft Cut invokes a random cut that does not upset the balance of the car. The Hard Cut disables all ignition or fuel above this engine speed. The optimum difference between the soft and hard cut is normally about 50 - 100 rpm.

name: 1D_WHEELSPEEDREVLIMITHCUTDIFFERENCE
long_desc: Soft to Hard Cut Difference used when the road speed rev limit is active. If the number is not in the range 0 -> 1023 rpm; the ECU will use a default of 300 rpm

name: 1D_PITLANESPEEDLIMIT
long_desc: Pit Lane Speed Limit in mph. The Pit Lane limiter will limit the car to this speed. If the pit lane rpm limits result in a lower speed then this then the rpm limits will take priority.

name: 1D_PITLANESOFTCUT
long_desc: Pit Lane Soft Cut in rpm. This is the soft limit for the speed limiter when the pit lane limiter is active. If the Pit Lane Speed Limit in mph results in a lower engine speed than this then the Pit Lane Speed Limit will take priority.

name: 1D_PITLANEHARDCUT
long_desc: Pit Lane Hard Cut in rpm. This is the hard limit for the speed limiter when the pit lane limiter is active. If the Pit Lane Speed Limit in mph results in a lower engine speed than this then the Pit Lane Speed Limit will take priority.

name: 1D_DRYSUMPTEMPTHRESHOLD
long_desc: Dry Sump Temperature Threshold. If either the temperature threshold or rev count threshold are exceeded the rev limit will be removed.

name: 1D_DRYSUMPREVCOUNTTHRESHOLD
long_desc: Dry Sump Rev Count Threshold. If either the temperature threshold or rev count threshold are exceeded the rev limit will be removed.

name: 1D_DRYSUMPREVLIMITUPPER
short_desc: Dry Sump Rev Limit Upper Speed
long_desc: Dry Sump Rev Limit Upper Speed. Above this speed no fuel will be allowed; limiting the engine speed

name: 1D_DRYSUMPREVLIMITLOWER
short_desc: Dry Sump Rev Limit Lower Speed
long_desc: Dry Sump Rev Limit Lower Speed. Below this speed fuel cut due to this limiter will be reinstated.

name: 1D_ENGINERUNTIMEREMAINING
long_desc: Engine Run Time Remaining. After this amount of running the ECU will use the Engine Run Time Rev Limit if it is lower than the standard rev limit. Set to maximum to disable this feature.

name: 1D_ENGINERUNTIMESOFTLIMIT
long_desc: Engine Run Time Soft Limit

name: 1D_ENGINERUNTIMEHARDLIMIT
long_desc: Engine Run Time Hard Limit

name: 1D_SETCRANKINGSWAPTIMER
long_desc: This is only applicable if the Engine Synch Method is set to "Swap Revs in Cranking". Set how long the ECU should wait before swapping Cranking by 360degrees Crank when engine is cranking.

name: 1D_ONLYSYNCHBELOWTHISTPS
long_desc: Only try to synchronise if the throttle position is below this site

name: 1D_ONLYSYNCHBELOWTHISSPEED
long_desc: Only try to synchronise if the engine speed is below this rpm

name: 1D_ONLYSYNCHABOVETHISSPEED
long_desc: Only try to synchronise if the engine speed is above this rpm

name: 1D_ONLYSYNCHABOVETHISREVCOUNT
short_desc: Only Synch after this number revs
long_desc: Only try to synchronise after the engine has done this number of revolutions

name: 1D_PRESSURESYNCHTHRESHOLD
long_desc: Only applicable if the Engine Synch Method is set to "Manifold Pressure". The ECU looks to see where the manifold pressure first goes below this pressure in order to synchronise to the engine.

name: 1D_FUELEACHCYCLETHRESHOLD
long_desc: Fuel Each Cycle Threshold. If Fuel Every Rev is enabled then the engine will always run Fuel Each Cycle above this threshold. This overrules the Fuel Every Rev Strategy 'Always'. At higher injector duty cycles time is lost if the injectors are opened each rev; by only opening each cycle better control of the fuel is achieved.

name: 1D_CAM1WINDOWOPENTOOTH
long_desc: Cam 1 Window Open (crank tooth) This section is only used  for engines with variable cam shafts fitted and Inductive cam sensors. Value must be set to maximum (255) in all other cases. Setting for Ford ST170 is Tooth 22.

name: 1D_CAM1WINDOWCLOSETOOTH
long_desc: Cam 1 Window Close (crank tooth) This section is only used  for engines with variable cam shafts fitted and Inductive cam sensors. Value must be set to maximum (255) in all other cases. Setting for Ford ST170 is Tooth 13.

name: 1D_CAM2WINDOWOPENTOOTH
long_desc: Cam 2 Window Open (crank tooth) This section is only used  for engines with variable cam shafts fitted and Inductive cam sensors. Value must be set to maximum (255) in all other cases.

name: 1D_CAM2WINDOWCLOSETOOTH
long_desc: Cam 2 Window Close (crank tooth) This section is only used  for engines with variable cam shafts fitted and Inductive cam sensors. Value must be set to maximum (255) in all other cases.

name: 1D_CAM1WINDOWOPENANGLE
long_desc: Cam 1 Window Open (Angle). Unless you are having problems with the cam input the cam window options should all be set to their maximums. If the engine will start and run but has problems once the engine synchronises to the cam then you may be able to use the cam window to fix the problem. For small single tooth and half moon cam wheels; record the <Measured Cam 1 Phase> with the engine runing whilst the engine is not synched. Subtract 60 from the Cam 1 phase and enter it into the <Cam 1 Window Open (Angle)> (if below zero add 360). Then put 80 in <Cam 1 Window Length (Angle)>

name: 1D_CAM1WINDOWLENGTHANGLE
long_desc: Cam 1 Window Length (Angle). Unless you are having problems with the cam input the cam window options should all be set to their maximums. If the engine will start and run but has problems once the engine synchronises to the cam then you may be able to use the cam window to fix the problem. For small single tooth and half moon cam wheels; record the <Measured Cam 1 Phase> with the engine runing whilst the engine is not synched. Subtract 60 from the Cam 1 phase and enter it into the <Cam 1 Window Open (Angle)> (if below zero add 360). Then put 80 in <Cam 1 Window Length (Angle)>

name: 1D_CAMCRANTRESETANGLE
short_desc: Cam Angle for Start With CAM
long_desc: Cam Angle for Start With CAM. ONLY FOR SINGLE TOOTH CAM SYSTEMS. This is the angle of the cam in degrees after TDC of the first cylinder to fire. If you start the engine without this feature then "Measured CAM 1 Phase" will give a very good aproximation of this the value needed (see note). Using this feature may help high compression engines or slow cranking engines to start. NOTE: A suggestion is to use "Measured CAM Phase 1" and subtract a number of degrees based on the number of teeth on the Crank Trigger wheel. For a 24 tooth crank wheel subtract 7; for 36 subtract 5 and for a 60 subtract 3.

name: 1D_THROTTLEANGLE1_3
long_desc: The maximum reading that would normally be seen on this input. If the reading exceeds this value the ECU will assume a fault condition and use the Default value. A fault will be flagged and the fault light turned on. To prevent a fault being generated when an input is unused set this value to its maximum.

long_desc: The minimum reading that would normally be seen on this input. If the reading goes below this value the ECU will assume a fault condition and use the Default value. A fault will be flagged and the fault light turned on. To prevent a fault being generated when an input is unused set this value to its minimum.

name: 1D_MINSEENTHROTTLE1_UL

name: 1D_MINSEENTHROTTLE1_LL

name: 1D_MINSEENTHROTTLE1_D

long_desc: The maximum reading that would normally be seen on this input. If the reading exceeds this value the ECU will assume a fault condition and use the Default value. A fault will be flagged and the fault light turned on. To prevent a fault being generated when an input is unused set this value to its maximum.

A fault will be flagged and the fault light turned on. To prevent a fault being generated when an input is unused set this value to its minimum.

name: 1D_MAPPINGPOT5_D
long_desc: The value that the ECU will use if the input is in fault condition. This does not have to be within the values specified as 'normal' in the upper and lower limits.

name: 1D_STRAINSHIFTUPABOVE
long_desc: Analogue Gear Shift Up Above. The ECU will interpret a voltage above this as an upshift request.

name: 1D_STRAINSHIFTHYSTERESIS
long_desc: Analogue Gear Shift Hysteresis. The shift request occurs at the voltages defined above; but is only released when the voltage has returned a further amount defined by this parameter.

name: 1D_TPSSITEFORIDLEIGN
short_desc: For Idle Ign TPS must be below
long_desc: Set the threshold that the TPS site must be below in order to use the Engine Temp at Idle Map.

name: 1D_PEDALSITEFORIDLEIGN
short_desc: For Idle Ign Pedal must be below
long_desc: Set the threshold that the Pedal site must be below in order to use the Engine Temp at Idle Map. If no pedal is fitted then set this map to its maximum value.

name: 1D_NOAIRTEMPLESSTHANTPS
short_desc: Inhibit Air Temp Ign comp below TPS
long_desc: Inhibit Air Temp Ign comp below TPS

name: 1D_DWELLTIME
long_desc: The length of time the coil is switched for. Note: this value is limited internaly to a maximum of 4 ms

name: 1D_COARSE(BIGGER#->EARLIERSPARK)
long_desc: Every time this number is increased by 1; the ignition will advance by 30� Any number bigger that 23 will be limited internally to 23.

name: 1D_FINE(BIGGER#->LATERSPARK)
long_desc: Allows 0 - 30� adjustment of the ignition timing. Note; this value does not take effect during cranking.

name: 1D_CRANKINGTOOTHOFFSET
long_desc: Determines ignition timing during cranking in steps of one crank tooth. Common Examples are:- VW I4; 2; GM/Opel/Vauxhall 0 ;Ford I4 0.

name: 1D_CRANKEXITSPEED_2
long_desc: The threshold at which the ECU changes from Cranking Maps to Running maps. Once the engine speed is above this number the ECU will not go back into cranking until the speed goes below the Crank Entry Speed. If the number is not in the range 350 -> 1000 rpm; the ECU will use a default of 650 rpm.

name: 1D_CRANKENTRYSPEED_2
long_desc: The threshold at which the ECU changes from Running maps to Cranking Maps. If the Engine speed is below this number the ECU will remain in cranking mode until the speed exceeds the Crank Exit Speed. If the number is not in the range 350 -> 1000 rpm; the ECU will use the Crank Exit Speed.

name: 1D_KNKIMMEDIATERETARD
long_desc: Amount of Retard on first detection of KNK

name: 1D_KNKMAXRETARD
long_desc: Maximum amount of retard due to Knk

name: 1D_POSTKNKREVS
long_desc: Number of Revs after initial Retard before Ignition Adavnce reinstatement or further retard if KNK still present

name: 1D_KNKADVANCERATE
long_desc: Rate at which Ignition is reinstated in  degrees per rev after a KNK event

name: 1D_BALANCEBANK1
long_desc: Balance for Bank 1

name: 1D_INTTIME
long_desc: Int Time

name: 1D_BALANCEBANK2
long_desc: Balance for Bank 2

name: 1D_COARSEKNK360
long_desc: KNK 360

name: 1D_KNOCKWINDOWWIDTH
long_desc: Number of teeth the Knock Chip integrates for

name: 1D_THROTTLEPERIODFORACCEL
long_desc: Defines how often the throttle is sampled during the acceleration detection.

name: 1D_ACCELTHRESHOLD
long_desc: No Accel / Decel fuel will be granted unless the rate of change of load is greater than this threshold.

name: 1D_ACCELFUELDECAYREVS
short_desc: Accel Fuel Decays every x Revs
long_desc: Accel Fuel Decays every x Revs

name: 1D_DECELFUELDECAYREVS
short_desc: Decel Fuel Decays every x Revs
long_desc: Decel Fuel Decays every x Revs

name: 1D_DECELFUELSCALING
long_desc: Set to 1 to run as pre Version 800 software.

name: 1D_BLATONLYUDERTPS
short_desc: Async Accel only below this TPS Site
long_desc: Async Accel only below this TPS Site

name: 1D_BLATINHIBITLAMBDATIMER
long_desc: Closed loop control will be suspended for this length of time after an Async Accel Event.

name: 1D_INJSTOPOFFSET
long_desc: Inj Stop Offset

name: 1D_OXYGENSENSOR1_3_2
long_desc: The maximum reading that would normally be seen on this input. If the reading exceeds this value the ECU will assume a fault condition and use the Default value. A fault will be flagged and the fault light turned on. To prevent a fault being generated when an input is unused set this value to its maximum.

A fault will be flagged and the fault light turned on. To prevent a fault being generated when an input is unused set this value to its minimum.

name: 1D_OXYGENSENSOR2_3_2

A fault will be flagged and the fault light turned on. To prevent a fault being generated when an input is unused set this value to its maximum.

name: 1D_OXYGENSENSOR2_2_2

A fault will be flagged and the fault light turned on. To prevent a fault being generated when an input is unused set this value to its minimum.

name: 1D_OXYGENSENSOR2_4
long_desc: The value that the ECU will use if the input is in fault condition. This does not have to be within the values specified as 'normal' in the upper and lower limits.

name: 1D_WARMUPTIMER
long_desc: The number of seconds delay; after starting the engine; before the closed loop lambda becomes operational. Used primarliy to allow the Lambda sensor(s) to reach operating temperature before initiating Closed Loop Fuel Control.

name: 1D_COOLANTTEMPTHRESHOLD
long_desc: Engine Coolant Tempeature is required to be over this temperature for Closed Loop Fueling Control to be activated.

name: 1D_TPSVARIANCETHRESHOLD
long_desc: An arbitary measure of the TPS stability. Used to inhibit Closed Loop Fuelling Control in the event that the TPS is not stable.

name: 1D_FUELPROPORTIONALGAIN
long_desc: Fuel Control Proportional Gain. Recommended setting is 90%/Lambda

name: 1D_FUELINTEGRALGAIN
long_desc: Fuel Control Integral Gain. Recommended setting is 5%/Lambda/sec

name: 1D_LAMBDAINTEGRALSTORELIMIT
long_desc: Short Term Trim Limit. This sets the limit for the short Term Trim. This works in both righ and lean directions. Anything over 37.5% is limited by the ECU to 37.5%

name: 1D_HIGHLOADLAMBDAINTEGRALSTORELIMIT
short_desc: High Load Short Term Trim Limit
long_desc: High Load Short Term Trim Limit. This sets the limit for the short Term Trim when the load input is above the <Lambda Short Term High Load Threshold>. This works in both righ and lean directions. Anything over 37.5% is limited by the ECU to 37.5%

name: 1D_LAMBDASHORTERMHIGHLOADTHRESHOLD
short_desc: Lambda Short Term High Load Threshold
long_desc: Lambda Short Term High Load Threshold. If the input load is above this threshold then the <High Load Short Term Trim Limit> is used instead of the <Short Term Trim Limit>

name: 1D_ONLYADAPTIFSPEEDWITHINSITE
short_desc: Only Adapt If Speed Within Site
long_desc: Only Adapt If Speed Within Site. This limits the adaption to altering the adaptive fuel map only when close to an exact speed site. If set to 0.1 then the speed must be within 0.1 of a site. If this value is greater than 0.5 then this will not limit the adaption.

name: 1D_ONLYADAPTIFLOADWITHINSITE
short_desc: Only Adapt If Load Within Load Site
long_desc: Only Adapt If Load Within Load Site. This limits the adaption to altering the adaptive fuel map only when close to an exact load site. If set to 0.1 then the load must be within 0.1 of a site. If this value is greater than 0.5 then this will not limit the adaption.

name: 1D_ONLYADAPTABOVECOOLANT
long_desc: Adapt Over Coolant Temp

name: 1D_ONLYADAPTUNDERCOOLANT
long_desc: Adapt Under Coolant Temp

name: 1D_ONLYADAPTABOVEAIRTEMP
long_desc: Adapt Over Air Temp

name: 1D_ONLYADAPTUNDERAIRTEMP
long_desc: Adapt Under Air Temp

name: 1D_ONLYADAPTOVERLOADSITE
long_desc: Adaptive Over Load Site. This is the minimum load site for the system to write to the adaptive map.

name: 1D_ONLYADAPTUNDERLOADSITE
long_desc: Adaptive Under Load Site. This is the maximum load site for the system to write to the adaptive map.

name: 1D_ADAPTIVEFUELLIMIT
long_desc: Adaptive Fuel Limit. This sets the maximum amount that the adaptive maps can alter the fuel by. This works in both rich and lean directions.

name: 1D_FUELADAPTTHRESHOLD
short_desc: Short to Long Term Trim Threshold
long_desc: Short to Long Term Trim Threshold. When The Short Term Trim exceeds this amount the adaptive map will be modified accordingly This is internally limited to 20%; anything over this value results in a Short to Long Term Trim Threshold of 3%

name: 1D_LAMBDA_ADAPTIONRATE
long_desc: Lambda Adaption Rate

name: 1D_BOOSTPGAIN
long_desc: The proportional gain for the closed loop boost control. Don't mess with this number without consulting MBE first.

name: 1D_BOOSTIGAIN
long_desc: The integral gain for the closed loop boost control. Don't mess with this number without consulting MBE first.

name: 1D_BOOSTDGAIN
long_desc: The differential gain for the closed loop boost control. Don't mess with this number without consulting MBE first.

name: 1D_WASTEGATEFREQUENCY
long_desc: The frequency of the PWM signal applied to the wastegate drive.

name: 1D_VCAM_PGAIN
long_desc: The gain for the proportional term in the control loop. You would not normally need to adjust this map. Suggested Values: Ford Zetec 60;

name: 1D_VCAM_IGAIN
long_desc: The gain for the integral term in the control loop. You would not normally need to adjust this map. Suggested Values: Ford Zetec 30;

name: 1D_VCAM_DGAIN
long_desc: The gain for the differential term in the control loop. You would not normally need to adjust this map. Suggested Values: Ford Zetec 0;

name: 1D_CAM1PHASEOFFSET
long_desc: Adjust this number to get zero in the Cam Phase realtime display when the cam shaft is at one end of its travel.

name: 1D_VARCAMPILOTDC
long_desc: Var Cam Pilot Duty Cycle. This is the base duty cycle that the control loop works from. It should be set to just less than the duty cycle needed for the cam to start moving. Suggested Values: Ford Zetec 85%;

name: 1D_EGASFAILUPPERSPEED
long_desc: The engine speed above which the fuel is cut if a fault is detected with the EGas unit. If this value is not less than 3500 rpm; the ECU will use a default value of 2000 rpm.

name: 1D_EGASFAILLOWERSPEED
long_desc: The engine speed below which the fuel is re-instated if a fault is detected with the EGas unit. If this value is not less than the upper speed threshold then the upper speed threshold less 50 rpm will be used here.

name: 1D_EGASA_RESTING_POS
long_desc: This represents the voltage read from the EGas Throttle Pot when there is no power applied. This value is adjusted at power up if necessary.

name: 1D_EGASB_RESTING_POS
long_desc: This represents the voltage read from the EGas Throttle Pot when there is no power applied. This value is adjusted at power up if necessary.

name: 1D_EGAS_DITHERAMOUNT
long_desc: EGas Dither Amount

name: 1D_EGAS_DITHERPERIOD
long_desc: EGas Dither Period in ms

name: 1D_EGASA_PERIODRANGE1
short_desc: EGas A Period Range 1 (0 up to 3.2 ms)
long_desc: Correpsonds to frequencies from infinite Hz down to 310 Hz. ONLY VALID IF RANGE 1 IS SELECTED

name: 1D_EGASA_PERIODRANGE2
short_desc: EGas A Period Range 2 (3.2 to 6.5 ms)
long_desc: Correpsonds to frequencies from 310 Hz down to 154Hz. ONLY VALID IF RANGE 3 IS SELECTED

name: 1D_EGASA_PERIODRANGE3
short_desc: EGas A Period Range 3 (6.5 to 200 ms)
long_desc: Correpsonds to frequencies from 154 Hz down to 5Hz. ONLY VALID IF RANGE 2 IS SELECTED

name: 1D_EGASA_PERIODRANGE4
short_desc: EGas A Period Range 4 (200 to 400 ms)
long_desc: Correpsonds to frequencies from 5 Hz down to 2.4Hz. ONLY VALID IF RANGE 4 IS SELECTED

name: 1D_SETIGNBANDATIDLE
long_desc: Set the size of the ign band at idle. This number is added AND subtracted from the idleal ign advance to give a max and a min

name: 1D_SETMAXIGNATIDLE
long_desc: The maximum number of degrees that the idle control will work to

name: 1D_SETMINIGNATIDLE
long_desc: The minimum number of degrees that the idle control will work to

name: 1D_IDLE_TPS_THRESHOLD
short_desc: Only do idle control below throttle site
long_desc: Sets the throttle site below which idle speed control will be enabled.

name: 1D_IDLE_ENGSPEED_THRESHOLD
short_desc: Max RPM above target to enter Idle Speed Control
long_desc: Max RPM above target to enter Idle Speed Control. <Target Idle Speed> + <This Value> is the RPM below which Idle Speed Control may become active. Once active; if the RPM exceeds this value+100 then the Idle Control will become inactive. A small value will allow the engine to go straight to the target idle speed; whilst a larger value will cause the engine to hang up and slow under idle control to the target speed.

name: 1D_IDLE_ROADSPEED_THRESHOLD
short_desc: Only do idle control below road speed
long_desc: Sets the road speed below which idle speed control will be enabled. Used to prevent idle control on long overruns where the revs may drop below the threshold (eg going down hill)

name: 1D_SET_IDLEWARMUPTIMER
long_desc: Set the number of seconds after engine start that idle speed control will be inhibited for.

name: 1D_IDLE_BUFFERZONE
long_desc: If the difference between engine speed and target speed is less than the amount specified here then the idle control is assumed to have reached its target.

name: 1D_IDLEIGNCLAMPMAX
long_desc: Sets the maxmimum ignition advance allowed during idle speed control.

name: 1D_IDLEIGNCLAMPMIN
long_desc: Sets the minimum ignition advance allowed during idle speed control.

name: 1D_IDLEIGNITIONPGAIN
long_desc: Idle Ignition P Gain. Suggested value of 0.06

name: 1D_IDLEIGNITIONIGAIN
long_desc: Idle Ignition I Gain. Suggested value of 0.010.

name: 1D_IDLEVALVEOPENLOOP
short_desc: Idle Valve Off Idle Duty Cycle
long_desc: Idle Valve Off Idle Duty Cycle. This is the duty cycle sent to the idle valve when not in idle control. It should be set small enough that the engine always returns to idle control yet large enough that the engine does not slow too quickly off throttle and stall.

name: 1D_IDLEVALVECRANKING
long_desc: Idle Valve Cranking Duty Cycle. This is the duty cycle sent to the idle valve when in cranking. This is to allow a different amount of air compared to the off idle setting to aid easier starting.

name: 1D_TARGETIGNITIONATIDLE
long_desc: Target Ignition At Idle. If the Air Control is enabled and the Engine Speed is within 25rpm of the Idle Target; the ECU will attempt to achieve this ignition by manipulating the Air; using the output defined in <Idle Air Closed Loop Output>. The ECU will aim to be within 2 degrees of the target ignition value.

name: 1D_IDLEINCREASEWITHAIRCON
short_desc: Target Idle Increase With Air Con
long_desc: Target Idle Increase With Air Con

name: 1D_EGASTARGETALOWERLIMIT
long_desc: The maximum voltage that the horizontal valve can be requested to go to.

name: 1D_EGASTARGETAUPPERLIMIT
long_desc: The minimum voltage that the horizontal valve can be requested to go to.

name: 1D_EGASTARGETBUPPERLIMIT
long_desc: The maximum voltage that the vertical valve can be requested to go to.

name: 1D_EGASTARGETBLOWERLIMIT
long_desc: The minimum voltage that the vertical valve can be requested to go to.

name: 1D_VALVEA_PERIODRANGE1
short_desc: Valve Period Range 1 (0 up to 3.2 ms)
long_desc: Correpsonds to frequencies from infinite Hz down to 310 Hz. ONLY VALID IF RANGE 1 IS SELECTED

name: 1D_VALVEA_PERIODRANGE2
long_desc: Correpsonds to frequencies from 310 Hz down to 154Hz. ONLY VALID IF RANGE 3 IS SELECTED

name: 1D_VALVEA_PERIODRANGE3
long_desc: Correpsonds to frequencies from 154 Hz down to 5Hz. ONLY VALID IF RANGE 2 IS SELECTED

name: 1D_VALVEA_PERIODRANGE4
long_desc: Correpsonds to frequencies from 5 Hz down to 2.4Hz. ONLY VALID IF RANGE 4 IS SELECTED

name: 1D_VALVEA_DEADBAND
long_desc: Horizontal Deadband

name: 1D_VALVEB_DEADBAND
long_desc: Vertical Deadband

name: 1D_FAULTS0FITTED
long_desc: Temp map

name: 1D_FAULTS1FITTED
long_desc: Temp map

name: 1D_INJECTORSFITTED
long_desc: Temp map

name: 1D_INJECTORSCOND1
long_desc: Temp map

name: 1D_FAULTCONDITION1VALUE
long_desc: Temp Map

name: 1D_HARDFROMSOFTLAUNCH1
long_desc: Sets how high the hard limiter is above the soft limit for Launch Sector 1. The higher this limiter is set the smoother launch will be. Recommended max value of 1023 RPM only reduce if RPM control is insufficient during launch

name: 1D_HARDFROMSOFTLAUNCH2
long_desc: Sets how high the hard limiter is above the soft limit for Launch Sector 2. The higher this limiter is set the smoother launch will be. Recommended max value of 1023 RPM only reduce if RPM control is insufficient during launch

name: 1D_HARDFROMSOFTLAUNCH3
long_desc: Sets how high the hard limiter is above the soft limit for Launch Sector 3. The higher this limiter is set the smoother launch will be. Recommended max value of 1023 RPM only reduce if RPM control is insufficient during launch

name: 1D_HARDFROMSOFTLAUNCH4
long_desc: Sets how high the hard limiter is above the soft limit for Launch Sector 4. The higher this limiter is set the smoother launch will be. Recommended max value of 1023 RPM only reduce if RPM control is insufficient during launch

name: 1D_HARDFROMSOFTLAUNCH5
long_desc: Sets how high the hard limiter is above the soft limit for Launch Sector 5. The higher this limiter is set the smoother launch will be. Recommended max value of 1023 RPM only reduce if RPM control is insufficient during launch

name: 1D_HARDFROMSOFTLAUNCH6
long_desc: Sets how high the hard limiter is above the soft limit for Launch Sector 6. The higher this limiter is set the smoother launch will be. Recommended max value of 1023 RPM only reduce if RPM control is insufficient during launch

name: 1D_HARDFROMSOFTLAUNCH7
long_desc: Sets how high the hard limiter is above the soft limit for Launch Sector 7. The higher this limiter is set the smoother launch will be. Recommended max value of 1023 RPM only reduce if RPM control is insufficient during launch

name: 1D_HARDFROMSOFTLAUNCH8
long_desc: Sets how high the hard limiter is above the soft limit for Launch Sector 8. The higher this limiter is set the smoother launch will be. Recommended max value of 1023 RPM only reduce if RPM control is insufficient during launch

name: 1D_TPSTHRESHOLDFORLAUNCHARM
long_desc: TPS Threshold to Arm Launch. The TPS Site must be less than this value to allow the system to arm the Launch Control. Recommend value Site 3.0

name: 1D_WHEELSPEEDTHRESHOLDFORLAUNCHARM
long_desc: Wheel speed Threshold to Arm Launch. The Wheel speed must be less than this value to allow the system to arm the Launch Control. Recommended value 5 mph

name: 1D_CRANKSPEEDTHRESHOLDFORLAUNCHARM
short_desc: Engine Speed Threshold to Arm Launch
long_desc: Engine Speed Threshold to Arm Launch. The engine speed must be less than this value to allow the system to arm the Launch Control. Recommended value 2000 RPM or 500 RPM above normal Idle speed. which ever is the higher.

name: 1D_SLIPTHRESHOLDTOCANCELLAUNCH
long_desc: Slip Threshold to Cancel Launch. If the slip falls below this value anytime after 0.1s of launch and the Wheelspeed Threshold is met then the launch control will be stopped and the engine allowed to run normally. This function is only active when Traction Control is enabled.

name: 1D_WHEELSPEEDTHRESHOLDFORLAUNCHCANCEL
long_desc: Wheelspeed Threshold to Cancel Launch. If the wheelspeed is above this value anytime after 0.1s of launch and the Slip Threshold is met then the launch control will be stopped and the engine allowed to run normally. This function is only active when Traction Control is enabled. (This value should be greater than <Min Wheel Speed For Traction> and must be greater than 5mph)

name: 1D_SPEEDDIFFERENCETHRESHOLDFORLAUNCHCANCEL
short_desc: Speed Difference Threshold to Cancel Launch
long_desc: Speed Difference Threshold to Cancel Launch. If the fron to rear wheelspeed difference  is below this value anytime after 0.1s of launch and the other thresholds are met then the launch control will be stopped and the engine allowed to run normally. This function is only active when Traction Control is enabled.

name: 1D_TRACTIONFROMLAUNCHTRANSITIONTIME
long_desc: Launch to Traction Control transition time. Once Launch has finished; this is the time taken for the ECU to gradually control the slip to the values demanded by the Traction Control. A long time gives a softer control and more wheelspin; a shorter will be harder but with less wheelspin. Recommended value 5000 ms.

name: 1D_LAUNCHLIMITERWITHTRACTION_SECTOR1
long_desc: Launch Limiter with Traction Sector 1. When Traction Control is enabled the single value launch limiters determine the rev limit at launch; and until the launch timer expires or the traction control takes over.

name: 1D_LAUNCHLIMITERWITHTRACTION_SECTOR2
long_desc: Launch Limiter with Traction Sector 2. When Traction Control is enabled the single value launch limiters determine the rev limit at launch; and until the launch timer expires or the traction control takes over.

name: 1D_LAUNCHLIMITERWITHTRACTION_SECTOR3
long_desc: Launch Limiter with Traction Sector 3. When Traction Control is enabled the single value launch limiters determine the rev limit at launch; and until the launch timer expires or the traction control takes over.

name: 1D_LAUNCHLIMITERWITHTRACTION_SECTOR4
long_desc: Launch Limiter with Traction Sector 4. When Traction Control is enabled the single value launch limiters determine the rev limit at launch; and until the launch timer expires or the traction control takes over.

name: 1D_LAUNCHLIMITERWITHTRACTION_SECTOR5
long_desc: Launch Limiter with Traction Sector 5. When Traction Control is enabled the single value launch limiters determine the rev limit at launch; and until the launch timer expires or the traction control takes over.

name: 1D_LAUNCHLIMITERWITHTRACTION_SECTOR6
long_desc: Launch Limiter with Traction Sector 6. When Traction Control is enabled the single value launch limiters determine the rev limit at launch; and until the launch timer expires or the traction control takes over.

name: 1D_LAUNCHLIMITERWITHTRACTION_SECTOR7
long_desc: Launch Limiter with Traction Sector 7. When Traction Control is enabled the single value launch limiters determine the rev limit at launch; and until the launch timer expires or the traction control takes over.

name: 1D_LAUNCHLIMITERWITHTRACTION_SECTOR8
long_desc: Launch Limiter with Traction Sector 8. When Traction Control is enabled the single value launch limiters determine the rev limit at launch; and until the launch timer expires or the traction control takes over.

name: 1D_LAUNCHSECTOR1LOW
long_desc: Set the lower voltage threshold for launch and traction sector 1

name: 1D_LAUNCHSECTOR1HIGH
long_desc: Set the upper voltage threshold for launch and traction sector 1

name: 1D_LAUNCHSECTOR2LOW
long_desc: Set the lower voltage threshold for launch and traction sector 2

name: 1D_LAUNCHSECTOR2HIGH
long_desc: Set the upper voltage threshold for launch and traction sector 2

name: 1D_LAUNCHSECTOR3LOW
long_desc: Set the lower voltage threshold for launch and traction sector 3

name: 1D_LAUNCHSECTOR3HIGH
long_desc: Set the upper voltage threshold for launch and traction sector 3

name: 1D_LAUNCHSECTOR4LOW
long_desc: Set the lower voltage threshold for launch and traction sector 4

name: 1D_LAUNCHSECTOR4HIGH
long_desc: Set the upper voltage threshold for launch and traction sector 4

name: 1D_LAUNCHSECTOR5LOW
long_desc: Set the lower voltage threshold for launch and traction sector 5

name: 1D_LAUNCHSECTOR5HIGH
long_desc: Set the upper voltage threshold for launch and traction sector 5

name: 1D_LAUNCHSECTOR6LOW
long_desc: Set the lower voltage threshold for launch and traction sector 6

name: 1D_LAUNCHSECTOR6HIGH
long_desc: Set the upper voltage threshold for launch and traction sector 6

name: 1D_LAUNCHSECTOR7LOW
long_desc: Set the lower voltage threshold for launch and traction sector 7

name: 1D_LAUNCHSECTOR7HIGH
long_desc: Set the upper voltage threshold for launch and traction sector 7

name: 1D_LAUNCHSECTOR8LOW
long_desc: Set the lower voltage threshold for launch and traction sector 8. If the voltage is in this sector then the LTC system is disabled.

name: 1D_LAUNCHSECTOR8HIGH
long_desc: Set the upper voltage threshold for launch and traction sector 8. If the voltage is in this sector then the LTC system is disabled.

name: 1D_FUELCOMPFORSLIPRETARD
short_desc: Fuel Comp per 10� in Slip Retard

name: 1D_RADFANSONOVERSPEED
long_desc: Rad Fan 1 and Rad Fan 2 control is enabled if the Engine Speed is Greater than or equal <Rad Fans Engine Speed Threshold>. Rad Fan 1 and Rad Fan 2 will be forced OFF at Engine Speeds Less than <Rad Fans Engine Speed Threshold>.

name: 1D_RUNONAFTERERT
long_desc: If this feature is enabled this is the time that the Engine has to run for before the Run on Timers will become active.

name: 1D_MAXFANRUNONTIMERSEED
short_desc: Max Fan and Water Pump Run On Time
long_desc: This is used as a safety mechanism to ensure that the system will shutdown (in order to save battery life) after Ignition OFF. This time should typically be set to the maximum time that you expect the Rad Fans and Water Pump drives to remain ON after Ignition OFF.

name: 1D_RADFAN1ONOVERTEMP
long_desc: The temperature above which Rad Fan 1 will be switched on during Engine Running. Note that this output will be available on a Pin as set in the "Programmable Pins"

name: 1D_RADFAN1OFFUNDERTEMP
long_desc: The temperature below which Rad Fan 1 will be switched off during normal engine running. Note that this output will be available on a Pin as set in the "Programmable Pins"

name: 1D_RADFAN1THRESHOLD
long_desc: If engine speed is below <Rad Fan 1 Engine Speed Threshold> and engine Temp is greater than <Rad Fan 1 Run ON Temperature> then the Rad Fan 1 Relay is held  ON. Note that this output will be available on a Pin as set in the "Programmable Pins"Ensure that <Rad Fan Relay Drives\Setup Information for both Fans\Max Fan Run On Time> is set accordingly.

name: 1D_RADFAN1SHUTDOWNTIME
long_desc: The length of time that Rad Fan 1 wil continue to run after Ignition Off. Ensure that <Basic Engine Setup\When Ign is Switched Off> is set accordingly. Ensure that <Rad Fan Relay Drives\Setup Information for both Fans\Max Fan Run On Time> is set accordingly.

name: 1D_RADFAN2ONOVERTEMP
long_desc: The temperature above which Rad Fan 2 will be switched on during normal engine running. Note that this output will be available on a Pin as set in the "Programmable Pins"

name: 1D_RADFAN2OFFUNDERTEMP
long_desc: The temperature below which Rad Fan 2 will be switched off. Note that this output will be available on a Pin as set in the "Programmable Pins"

name: 1D_RADFAN2RUNONTEMP
long_desc: If engine speed is below <Rad Fan 2 Engine Speed Threshold> and engine Temp is greater than <Rad Fan 2 Run ON Temperature> then the Rad Fan 2 relay  is held ON. Note that this output will be available on a Pin as set in the "Programmable Pins".Ensure that <Rad Fan Relay Drives\Setup Information for both Fans\Max Fan Run On Time> is set accordingly.

name: 1D_RADFAN2SHUTDOWNTIME
long_desc: The length of time that Rad Fan 2 wil continue to run after Ignition Off. Ensure that <Basic Engine Setup\When Ign is Switched Off> is set accordingly.Ensure that <Rad Fan Relay Drives\Setup Information for both Fans\Max Fan Run On Time> is set accordingly.

name: 1D_DIRECTRADFANTHRESHOLD
long_desc: If engine speed is below <Water Pump Engine Speed Threshold> and engine Temp is greater than <Water Pump Run ON Temperature>then the Water Pump Duty Cycle is derived from <Water Pump Duty Cycle Engine Stopped>. Note that this output will be available on a Pin as set in the "Programmable Pins"

name: 1D_DIRECTRADFANENGSPEED
long_desc: If engine speed is below <Water Pump Engine Speed Threshold> and engine Temp is greater than <Water Pump Temp Threshold>then the Water Pump Duty Cycle is derived from <Water Pump Duty Cycle Engine Stopped>. Note that this output will be available on a Pin as set in the "Programmable Pins"

name: 1D_RADFAN_PERIODRANGE1
short_desc: Rad Fan Period Range 1 (0 up to 3.2 ms)
long_desc: Correpsonds to frequencies from infinite Hz down to 310 Hz. ONLY VALID IF RANGE 1 IS SELECTED

name: 1D_RADFAN_PERIODRANGE2
short_desc: Rad Fan Period Range 2 (3.2 to 6.5 ms)
long_desc: Correpsonds to frequencies from 310 Hz down to 154Hz. ONLY VALID IF RANGE 3 IS SELECTED

name: 1D_RADFAN_PERIODRANGE3
short_desc: Rad Fan Period Range 3 (6.5 to 200 ms)
long_desc: Correpsonds to frequencies from 154 Hz down to 5Hz. ONLY VALID IF RANGE 2 IS SELECTED

name: 1D_RADFAN_PERIODRANGE4
short_desc: Rad Fan Period Range 4 (200 to 400 ms)
long_desc: Correpsonds to frequencies from 5 Hz down to 2.4Hz. ONLY VALID IF RANGE 4 IS SELECTED

name: 1D_ENGINESTOPPEDDC
short_desc: Water Pump Duty Cycle Engine Stopped
long_desc: If engine speed is below <Water Pump Engine Speed Threshold> and engine Temp is greater than <Water Pump Temp Threshold>then the Water Pump Duty Cycle is derived from <Water Pump Duty Cycle Engine Stopped>. Note that this output will be available on a Pin as set in the "Programmable Pins"

name: 1D_PWMWATERPUMPMINPWMWITHAC
short_desc: Water Pump Min Duty Cycle With Air Con
long_desc: Water Pump Min Duty Cycle With Air Con

name: 1D_WATERPUMPTHRESHOLD
long_desc: If the engine is below a certain speed then the Water Pump will carry on running until the coolant temperature is below this threshold.. Note that this output will be available on a Pin as set in the "Programmable Pins"

name: 1D_WATERPUMPENGSPEED
long_desc: If the engine is below this speed then the Water Pump will carry on running until the coolant temperature is below a threshold.

name: 1D_WATERPUMP_PERIODRANGE1
short_desc: Water Pump Period Range 1 (0 up to 3.2 ms)
long_desc: Correpsonds to frequencies from infinite Hz down to 310 Hz. ONLY VALID IF RANGE 1 IS SELECTED

name: 1D_WATERPUMP_PERIODRANGE2
short_desc: Water Pump Period Range 2 (3.2 to 6.5 ms)
long_desc: Correpsonds to frequencies from 310 Hz down to 154Hz. ONLY VALID IF RANGE 3 IS SELECTED

name: 1D_WATERPUMP_PERIODRANGE3
short_desc: Water Pump Period Range 3 (6.5 to 200 ms)
long_desc: Correpsonds to frequencies from 154 Hz down to 5Hz. ONLY VALID IF RANGE 2 IS SELECTED

name: 1D_WATERPUMP_PERIODRANGE4
short_desc: Water Pump Period Range 4 (200 to 400 ms)
long_desc: Correpsonds to frequencies from 5 Hz down to 2.4Hz. ONLY VALID IF RANGE 4 IS SELECTED

name: 1D_PSCUTTIME
long_desc: Given all conditions have been met to invoke a powershift this determines the length of time to cut ignition (in ms) from the falling edge of the Powershift Request Input Signal. name: 1D_PSLOCKOUTTIME

name: 1D_POSTLIMITERPSEXTENSION

name: 1D_AIRCONDELAYTIMER
long_desc: The air con relay will only be active after the engine has been running for this number of seconds.

name: 1D_AIRCONTPSSITE
short_desc: A/C only up to this Throttle Site
long_desc: The Air Con compressor will be switched off if the Throttle Site exceeds the value entered here. This would normally be wide open throttle.

name: 1D_AIRCONFANSROADSPEED
short_desc: A/C Fans on below Road Speed
long_desc: When the A/C compressor switches on the Rad Fans will also switch on if the road speed is below the threshold set here. To disable this feature enter zero here.

name: 1D_AIRCONINCREASEEGAS
long_desc: To help maintain the idle speed when the Air Con is switched on the ECU can increase the base EGas position that the idle speed controllor uses as the start point. This value specifiec the voltage to be added. Enter zero if this feature is not required.

name: 1D_AIRCONINCREASEIDLE
long_desc: If the idle speed is to increase when the air con switches on then the increase can be added here. The ECU rounds this speed increase to an even number. If this feature is not required then enter zero here.

name: 1D_HYDPUMPONBELOW
short_desc: Turn Pump on below this pressure
long_desc: Turn Pump on below this pressure.

name: 1D_HYDPUMPOFFABOVE
short_desc: Turn Pump off above this pressure
long_desc: Turn Pump off above this pressure.

name: 1D_LAUNCHSOFTCUT
long_desc: Specify the soft rev limit in launch mode

name: 1D_LAUNCHHARDCUT
long_desc: Specify the hard rev limit in launch mode

name: 1D_COOLANTTEMPFORDRYSUMP
short_desc: Only impose limit below coolant temp
long_desc: Specify the coolant temperature below which the rev limit is to be applied

name: 1D_DRYSUMPREVCOUNT
short_desc: Only impose limit until number of revs
long_desc: Specify the number of revolutions of the engine below which this rev limit will be imposed

name: 1D_DRYSUMPUPPERSPEED
long_desc: Specify the speed above which the fuel is to be cut.

name: 1D_DRYSUMPLOWERSPEED
long_desc: Specify the speed below which the fuel is to be reinstated

name: 1D_MISFIRELOWRPM
long_desc: The lowest engine speed at which the misfire inducer must work

name: 1D_MISFIREHIGHRPM
long_desc: The highest engine speed at which the misfire inducer must work

name: 1D_MISFIRELOWTPS
long_desc: The lowest throttle site at which the misfire inducer must work

name: 1D_MISFIREHIGHTPS
long_desc: The highest throttle site at which the misfire inducer must work

name: 1D_MINWHEELSPEEDFORTRACTION
long_desc: This is the minimum wheel speed for traction to occur. Recommended value is 5 MPH

name: 1D_MINTHROTTLESITEFORTRACTION
long_desc: This is the minimum throttle site for Traction Control to be active. Recommended Site 2.0

name: 1D_MINSOFTCUTTRACTIONLIMIT
long_desc: Minimum Soft Cut Traction Limit (Anti Stall). If the Rev Limit Traction calculates a lower Rev Limit than this value; then it is limited to this value. This is to ensure the engine does not bog down or stall.

name: 1D_MINHARDCUTTRACTIONLIMIT
long_desc: Minimum Hard Cut Traction Limit (Anti Stall) . If the Rev Limit Traction calculates a lower Rev Limit than this value; then it is limited to this value. This is to ensure the engine does not bog down or stall.

name: 1D_PSDISABLEPSBELOWSPEED
long_desc: Disable Powershift below engine speed. This function only disables Powershift Control; If using Gearbox Control this will not effect Solenoid controls

name: 1D_POWERSHIFTDELAY
long_desc: Powershift Debounce. This is the delay time from the user pressing the shift button (pin going low) before the powershift will start. If the button is released during this time no shift will happen. Used to ensure user does not make any accidental shifts.

name: 1D_PSCONTINUOUSASSERT
long_desc: Powershift Continuous Assert. The length of time the user will have to press the shift button (pin going low) after the shift has started before the powershift will continue when the button is released. Releasing the button before this timer has finished will cause the shift to end early. This will normally be set to 0. This is not used in "Cut On Pin Low"

name: 1D_PS_TPS_THRESHOLD_FOR_MULTICUT
long_desc: TPS threshold for Gearbox Relax. If below this threshold then Gearbox Relax function will occur. If above threshold then only the Powershift will happen. For Gearbox Control set to Site 7.0. Disable for normal Powershift by setting to Site 0.0

name: 1D_POWERSHIFTCUTTIME
long_desc: Upshift Gearbox Relax Cut Time. Allows the gearbox to relax before the gear change begins

name: 1D_POWERSHIFTTORQUEREDUCTION1
long_desc: Upshift Gearbox Relax Torque Reduction. This is the amount of retard to apply in torque reduction mode. 100% reduction will move the ignition timing to the zero torque point defined in the <Torque Reduction System> section.

name: 1D_POWERSHIFTDELAY2
long_desc: Powershift Delay. This is the delay from the end of the Gearbox Relax Period to the start of the Powershift. Normally 2 sparks are sufficient to apply the correct load to the gearbox before Powershift begins; Only used for full Gearbox Control Set to 0 for all other Powershift types

name: 1D_POWERSHIFTCUT2TIME
long_desc: Powershift Cut Time. If using 'Enabled + Complete on Target Gear' recommended value is 175m.s. to 250m.s; If using a 'Single Cut Time' recommended starting value is 100m.s. to 125m.s.

name: 1D_POWERSHIFTTORQUEREDUCTION2
long_desc: Powershift Torque Reduction. This is the amount of retard to apply in torque reduction mode. 100% reduction will move the ignition timing to the zero torque point defined in the <Torque Reduction System> section.

name: 1D_PSTORQUERECOVERYPERIOD2
long_desc: Powershift Torque Recovery Period. If Powershift Torque Reduction is being used this is the number of sparks that the Percentage Powershift Torque Reduction will recover to the normal Ignition advance over; If set to Zero there will be no recovery period; Recommended value is normally 6 sparks

name: 1D_POWERSHIFTCONFIRMTHRESHOLD
long_desc: Confirm Upshift Drum Rotation Threshold. Only available in Finish on target gear modes. Once the <Confirm Upshift Drum Rotation Timeout> has expired; if the shift has completed less than this threshold then the shift is flagged as a failure and it may be retried. If set to zero then no retry will happen.

name: 1D_POWERSHIFTFAILURETIMEOUT
long_desc: Confirm Upshift Drum Rotation Timeout. Only available in Finish on target gear modes. This is the time after <Powershift Cut Time> starts that the system will check to see that the shift is actually happening. The drum must have moved an amount towards the next gear; set by <Confirm Upshift Drum Rotation Threshold>. If not then the ECU will restart the shift after <Powershift Retry Delay> at begining of <Powershift Cut Time>. This feature will only work if the <Power Shift Configuration> is set to include "Complete on Target Gear".

name: 1D_PERCENTAGEGEARCOMPLETETOFINISHCUT
long_desc: Finish Upshift Drum Rotation Threshold. Only available in Finish on target gear modes. Recomended value 70% to 80%. Set to 100% for this function to have no effect.

name: 1D_POWERSHIFTRETRYDELAY
long_desc: Powershift Retry Delay. Only available in Finish on target gear modes. In the event of a shift failing to happen this is the number of sparks that will happen before Powershift is retried. Normally 1 spark is Sufficient to reapply load to the gearbox ready for the Powershift to start again.

name: 1D_POWERSHIFTMAXRETRIES
long_desc: Powershift Max Retries. Only available in Finish on target gear modes. This is the maximum number of times the ECU will retry a powershift after it has failed. If set to zero no retry will happen.

name: 1D_POSTPOWERSHIFTLOCKOUT
long_desc: Post Powershift Lockout. This is the amount of time after a gearchange has finished before another can be started. This helps prevent accidental double shifts. If using Gearbox Control this also allows time for the actuators to relax and the gear lever to return to centre.  This timer is diabled if <Active Gear Lever Return on Upshift> is Enabled. Recommended value 200 m.s. If more time is required use  Active Gear Lever Return to speed up gearchange.

name: 1D_POWERSHIFTMAXSOLENOIDTIME
long_desc: Maximum Shift Time. This is the maximum amount of time that the ECU will allow the gearshift to take. When this time has been reached the shift will be cancelled. If set to maximum then this feature will be disabled and no time limit applied to the shift.

name: 1D_USERDISABLEDSBELOWSPEED
short_desc: Disable Downshift Cut below engine speed
long_desc: Disable Downshift Control below engine speed. This function only disables spark control during downshifts. This will not effect the ECUs Gearbox Control of the Solenoids

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTDELAY
long_desc: Downshift Debounce. This is the delay time from the user pressing the shift button (pin going low) before the downshift will start. If the button is released during this time no shift will happen. Used to ensure user does not make any accidental shifts.

name: 1D_DSCONTINUOUSASSERT
long_desc: Downshift Continuous Assert. The length of time the user will have to press the shift button (pin going low) after the shift has started before the downshift will continue when the button is released. Releasing the button before this timer has finished will cause the shift to end early. This will normally be set to 0.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTCUTTIME
long_desc: Downshift Gearbox Relax Time. This is the time an engine spark cut or torque reduction will happen for; it allows the gearbox to relax; so that the solenoids can move the gearbox out ot gear.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTTORQUEREDUCTION1
long_desc: Downshift Gearbox Relax Torque Reduction. This is the amount of retard to apply in torque reduction mode. 100% reduction will move the ignition timing to the zero torque point defined in the <Torque Reduction System> section.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTCONFIRMTHRESHOLD
long_desc: Confirm Downshift Drum Rotation Threshold. Only available in Finish on target Gear modes. Once the Failure Timeout has expired; if the shift has completed less than this threshold then the shift is flagged as a failure and it may be retried. If set to zero then no retry will happen. Recommended value 30%

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTFAILURETIMEOUT
long_desc: Confirm Downshift Drum Rotation Timeout. This timer starts after <Downshift Gearbox Relax Time> has finished. On completion of <Confirm Downshift Drum Rotation Timeout> The system will check  the <Confirm Downshift Drum Rotation Threshold> to see that the shift is actually happening. If not then the ECU will perform a downshift retry using the retry settings. This timer will be restarted after the <Downshift Retry Relax Time> has finished. This will be repeated up to <Downshift Max Retries>.

name: 1D_PERCENTAGEGEARCOMPLETETOFINISHCUTDS
long_desc: Finish Downshift Drum Rotation Threshold. Only available in Finish on target gear modes. Recommended value 70%  Set to 100% for this function to have no effect.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTCUT2TIME
long_desc: Downshift Retry Relax Time. This is the number of sparks that the ECU will either remove or that the Torque Reduction operate for. This function will only be used if the system retries for a downshift.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTTORQUEREDUCTION2
long_desc: Downshift Retry Torque Reduction. This is the amount of retard to apply in torque reduction mode. 100% reduction will move the ignition timing to the zero torque point defined in the <Torque Reduction System> section.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTMAXRETRIES
long_desc: Downshift Max Retries. This is the maximum number of times the ECU will retry a downshift after it has failed. If set to zero no retry will happen. Recommended value 1 retry.

name: 1D_POSTDOWNSHIFTLOCKOUT
long_desc: Post Downshift Lockout. This is the amount of time after a gearchange has finished before another can be started. This allows time for the actuators  to relax and the gear lever to return to centre.  This timer is diabled if <Active Gear Lever Return on Downshift> is Enabled; Recommended value 200ms. If more time is required use Active Gear Lever Return to speed up gearchange.

name: 1D_POWERSHIFTMAXSOLENOIDTIME_2
long_desc: Maximum Shift Time. This is the maximum amount of time that the ECU will allow the gearshift to take. When this time has been reached the shift will be cancelled. If set to maximum then this feature will be disabled and no time limit applied to the shift.

name: 1D_GENERICOUTPUT1ONOVERBATTVOLTS
short_desc: Gen O/P1 On Over Battery Voltage
long_desc: The output will be turned ON if all ON Conditions are met i.e. the parameter is greater than or equal to the threshold. The output will be turned OFF if at least one of the OFF conditions are met i.e. less than or equal to the threshold.

name: 1D_GENERICOUTPUT1OFFUNDERBATTVOLTS
short_desc: Gen O/P1 Off Under Battery Voltage
long_desc: The output will be turned ON if all ON Conditions are met i.e. the parameter is greater than or equal to the threshold. The output will be turned OFF if at least one of the OFF conditions are met i.e. less than or equal to the threshold.

name: 1D_LAMBDAHOLDOFFTIME
long_desc: Lambda Hold Off Time. This is the time from the conditions for lambda control being met to the control actually starting.

name: 1D_EGT_UL
long_desc: EGT Upper Limit

name: 1D_EGT_LL
long_desc: EGT Lower Limit

name: 1D_EGT_D
long_desc: EGT Default

name: 1D_ANTILAG_ENABLEDABOVETHISSPEED
long_desc: Anti-Lag enabled above this speed

name: 1D_ANTILAG_DISABLEDBELOWTHISSPEED
long_desc: Anti-Lag disabled below this speed

name: 1D_ANTILAG_ENABLEDBELOWTHISTPS
short_desc: Anti-Lag enabled below this throttle site
long_desc: Anti-Lag enabled below this throttle site

name: 1D_ANTILAG_DISABLEDABOVETHISTPS
short_desc: Anti-Lag disabled above this throttle site
long_desc: Anti-Lag disabled above this throttle site

name: 1D_DS_TPS_THRESHOLD_FOR_ON_THROTTLE_SHIFT_RPM_LIMITS
short_desc: TPS threshold for On Throttle RPM shift limits
long_desc: TPS threshold for On Throttle RPM shift limits. If equal to or below this threshold then the ECU will use the Off Throttle RPM downshift limits. If above this threshold then the On Throttle RPM downshift limits are used.

name: 1D_GEARBOXSENSORFAILDSLIMIT
short_desc: GearBox Pot Failure Downshift RPM Limit
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit applied if the Gear Position sensor fails. The ECU will also apply the downshift limit into 1st gear from either the off throttle must release or on throttle maps depending on the throttle state. So whichever RPM limit of this or the shift to 1st will be used.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITIN8TH
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 8th. When in EIGHTH gear; this is the maximum engine speed at which a downshift into seventh is allowed. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITIN7TH
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 7th. When in SEVENTH gear; this is the maximum engine speed at which a downshift into sixth is allowed. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITIN6TH
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 6th. When in SIXTH gear; this is the maximum engine speed at which a downshift into fourth is allowed. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITIN5TH
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 5th. When in FIFTH gear; this is the maximum engine speed at which a downshift into fourth is allowed. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITIN4TH
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 4th. When in FOURTH gear; this is the maximum engine speed at which a downshift into third is allowed. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITIN3RD
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 3rd. When in THIRD gear; this is the maximum engine speed at which a downshift into second is allowed. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITIN2ND
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 2nd. When in SECOND gear; this is the maximum engine speed at which a downshift into first is allowed. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITIN8THONTHROTTLE
short_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 8th on Throttle
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 8th on Throttle. When in EIGHTH gear; this is the maximum engine speed at which a downshift into seventh is allowed. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITIN7THONTHROTTLE
short_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 7th on Throttle
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 7th on Throttle. When in SEVENTH gear; this is the maximum engine speed at which a downshift into seventh is allowed. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITIN6THONTHROTTLE
short_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 6th on Throttle
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 6th on Throttle. When in SIXTH gear; this is the maximum engine speed at which a downshift into seventh is allowed. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITIN5THONTHROTTLE
short_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 5th on Throttle
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 5th on Throttle. When in FIFTH gear; this is the maximum engine speed at which a downshift into seventh is allowed. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITIN4THONTHROTTLE
short_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 4th on Throttle
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 4th on Throttle. When in FOURTH gear; this is the maximum engine speed at which a downshift into seventh is allowed. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITIN3RDONTHROTTLE
short_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 3rd on Throttle
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 3rd on Throttle. When in THIRD gear; this is the maximum engine speed at which a downshift into seventh is allowed. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITIN2NDONTHROTTLE
short_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 2nd on Throttle
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit in 2nd on Throttle. When in SECOND gear; this is the maximum engine speed at which a downshift into seventh is allowed. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITTO7TH
short_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 7th - Must Release
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 7th. When shifting to SEVENTH gear; this is the maximum allowed engine speed the engine will be at after the shift into seventh. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITTO6TH
short_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 6th - Must Release
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 6th. When shifting to SIXTH gear; this is the maximum allowed engine speed the engine will be at after the shift into sixth. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITTO5TH
short_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 5th - Must Release
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 5th. When shifting to FIFTH gear; this is the maximum allowed engine speed the engine will be at after the shift into fifth. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITTO4TH
short_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 4th - Must Release
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 4th. When shifting to FOURTH gear; this is the maximum allowed engine speed the engine will be at after the shift into fourth. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITTO3RD
short_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 3rd - Must Release
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 3rd. When shifting to THIRD gear; this is the maximum allowed engine speed the engine will be at after the shift into third. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITTO2ND
short_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 2nd - Must Release
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 2nd. When shifting to SECOND gear; this is the maximum allowed engine speed the engine will be at after the shift into second. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITTO1ST
short_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 1st - Must Release
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 1st. When shifting to FIRST gear; this is the maximum allowed engine speed the engine will be at after the shift into first. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored. If the gearbox pot has failed then this limit will be used to prevent downshifts at high rpm.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITTO7TH_AUTOPADDLE
short_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 7th - Timed Paddle
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 7th. When shifting to SEVENTH gear; this is the maximum allowed engine speed the engine will be at after the shift into seventh. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITTO6TH_AUTOPADDLE

long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 6th. When shifting to SIXTH gear; this is the maximum allowed engine speed the engine will be at after the shift into sixth. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITTO5TH_AUTOPADDLE

long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 5th. When shifting to FIFTH gear; this is the maximum allowed engine speed the engine will be at after the shift into fifth. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITTO4TH_AUTOPADDLE

long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 4th. When shifting to FOURTH gear; this is the maximum allowed engine speed the engine will be at after the shift into fourth. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITTO3RD_AUTOPADDLE

long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 3rd. When shifting to THIRD gear; this is the maximum allowed engine speed the engine will be at after the shift into third. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITTO2ND_AUTOPADDLE
short_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 2nd - Timed Paddle
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 2nd. When shifting to SECOND gear; this is the maximum allowed engine speed the engine will be at after the shift into second. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITTO1ST_AUTOPADDLE
short_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 1st - Timed Paddle
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 1st. When shifting to FIRST gear; this is the maximum allowed engine speed the engine will be at after the shift into first. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITTO7THONTHROTTLE
short_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 7th on Throttle
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 7th on Throttle. When shifting to SEVENTH gear; this is the maximum allowed engine speed the engine will be at after the shift into seventh. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITTO6THONTHROTTLE
short_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 6th on Throttle
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 6th on Throttle. When shifting to SIXTH gear; this is the maximum allowed engine speed the engine will be at after the shift into sixth. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITTO5THONTHROTTLE
short_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 5th on Throttle
long_desc: Downshift RPM Limit to 5th on Throttle. When shifting to FIFTH gear; this is the maximum allowed engine speed the engine will be at after the shift into fifth. If the engine speed is equal to or higher than this threshold; the downshift request will be ignored.

name: 1D_DOWNSHIFTRPMLIMITTO1STONTHROTTLE

name: 1D_TRACTIONPOSPGAIN
long_desc: Traction Positive P Gain. This is the Reactive part of the PID control Loop. Increase this for a more assertive power cut to regain traction after it has been lost. This should be the same as the Negative P Gain. Suggested value 12%/rpm

name: 1D_TRACTIONNEGPGAIN
long_desc: Traction Negative P Gain. This is the Reactive part of the PID control Loop. This should be set to the same as the Positive P Gain. Increasing this delays the point at which the Predictive D Term comes in. Suggested value 12%/rpm

name: 1D_TRACTIONINTGAIN
long_desc: Traction Integral Gain. This is the Adaptive part of the PID control Loop. This is the part of the system that works over time to hold the level of slip at the target amount. Too low and the system will take a long time to settle and too high and the system will oscillate either side of the target. This needs to be set in balance with the P Gains. Suggested Value 22%/rpm/s

name: 1D_TRACTIONDIFFGAIN
long_desc: Traction Differential Gain. This is the Predictive part of the PID control loop. This detects the rise in slip before the target level of slip is reached; and cuts the engine power so that the wheels can be held at the target slip. This part also allows extra power back when the wheels gain more traction. Increasing this value will allow a harder and earlier initial power reduction and also allow the power back in earlier when traction is regained. Suggested value 125 % / (d mph/d ms)

name: 1D_TRACTIONOPENLOOP
long_desc: Traction Open Loop. This is an offset provided for when the system is not using the Integral Gain. When The Integral gain is in use this should be set to 0.

name: 2D_ACCELFUELDECAYMAP

name: 2D_BLATFUELFACTOR
